1
00:00:00,570 --> 00:00:04,070
<i>I love seeing
how girls from a happy household look</i>

2
00:00:04,070 --> 00:00:08,880
<i>when they make that look of despair.</i>

3
00:00:08,880 --> 00:00:10,580
The necklace is gone.

4
00:00:10,580 --> 00:00:12,530
Are you accusing me of stealing it?

5
00:00:12,530 --> 00:00:14,790
- You're mistaken.
- Did you get that girl?

6
00:00:14,790 --> 00:00:17,590
Don't tell me you're actually struggling?

7
00:00:17,590 --> 00:00:18,810
Shut up.

8
00:00:18,810 --> 00:00:20,670
Just hand over the cash.

9
00:00:20,670 --> 00:00:23,250
I wish I'd never given birth to you.

10
00:00:23,250 --> 00:00:25,400
You useless thing!

11
00:00:27,790 --> 00:00:30,190
He's a very important person to me!

12
00:00:30,190 --> 00:00:33,760
Don't ever do anything like this
to Mr. Chiaki again.

13
00:00:33,760 --> 00:00:37,480
Mr. Chiaki, are you okay?

14
00:00:37,480 --> 00:00:39,450
Please.

15
00:00:39,450 --> 00:00:40,870
Don't move.

16
00:00:40,870 --> 00:00:42,550
Stay with me.

17
00:00:50,350 --> 00:00:53,760
I'm sorry, Ama.

18
00:00:54,666 --> 00:00:56,116
It's okay.

19
00:00:58,100 --> 00:01:00,590
That's my mother.

20
00:01:01,830 --> 00:01:03,940
Hard to believe, right?

21
00:01:07,210 --> 00:01:11,460
After she got pregnant with me,

22
00:01:11,460 --> 00:01:14,220
the guy who was my father left her.

23
00:01:15,200 --> 00:01:18,780
It's all because of you
that my life is a mess!

24
00:01:18,780 --> 00:01:22,580
<i>That's why she treated me so harshly
since I was a kid.</i>

25
00:01:22,580 --> 00:01:24,550
Hey, isn't that abuse?

26
00:01:24,550 --> 00:01:27,720
- Should we report her?
- You shouldn't.

27
00:01:28,370 --> 00:01:31,420
<i>The nearby adults all turned a blind eye.</i>

28
00:01:34,530 --> 00:01:38,880
<i>So when a scout approached me at 14,
I jumped at the chance.</i>

29
00:01:40,110 --> 00:01:43,730
I thought I was finally free, but...

30
00:01:44,670 --> 00:01:49,970
she started coming to me for money,
saying, "Repay me for raising you".

31
00:01:51,850 --> 00:01:53,950
It's laughable, isn't it?

32
00:01:57,280 --> 00:01:59,870
I'm stronger than her now.

33
00:02:01,690 --> 00:02:06,780
But whenever I hear her voice, I can't move.

34
00:02:08,940 --> 00:02:10,860
It's pathetic.

35
00:02:13,230 --> 00:02:17,930
There's nothing pathetic about that.

36
00:02:29,970 --> 00:02:31,930
It hurt, didn't it?

37
00:02:32,810 --> 00:02:34,520
I'm sorry.

38
00:02:36,200 --> 00:02:37,810
But...

39
00:02:39,160 --> 00:02:41,710
I was really happy.

40
00:02:47,580 --> 00:02:49,390
Until now,

41
00:02:50,040 --> 00:02:54,010
no one around me
has ever bothered to save me.

42
00:02:56,690 --> 00:02:59,440
<i>No matter how poor we were,</i>

43
00:02:59,440 --> 00:03:02,630
<i>my family was what kept me going.</i>

44
00:03:04,180 --> 00:03:09,150
<i>But, Mr. Chiaki has always been alone.</i>

45
00:03:21,145 --> 00:03:23,095
It's okay.

46
00:03:24,610 --> 00:03:27,370
If anything happens,

47
00:03:27,370 --> 00:03:30,630
I promise I'll protect you.

48
00:03:33,040 --> 00:03:35,000
Really?

49
00:03:36,920 --> 00:03:38,290
Yes.

50
00:03:43,500 --> 00:03:45,170
Thank you.

51
00:03:46,605 --> 00:03:50,765
You're a kind person, Ama.

52
00:04:09,150 --> 00:04:11,460
Mr. Hosho, you're up soon.

53
00:04:12,570 --> 00:04:14,420
Mr. Hosho?

54
00:04:16,882 --> 00:04:19,384
Yeah, sorry.

55
00:04:31,250 --> 00:04:33,880
<i>You're sleeping so peacefully,</i>

56
00:04:33,880 --> 00:04:36,390
<i>I'll leave without waking you.</i>

57
00:04:38,290 --> 00:04:42,260
Hey, Chiaki, stay a little longer.

58
00:04:42,260 --> 00:04:43,920
No.

59
00:04:44,520 --> 00:04:47,330
I can't sleep around others.

60
00:05:46,920 --> 00:05:49,560
She's so shameless.

61
00:05:49,560 --> 00:05:51,990
I would've quit a long time ago.

62
00:05:52,850 --> 00:05:55,520
Hey! You can hear me, right?

63
00:05:55,520 --> 00:05:57,680
Don't you feel any guilt?

64
00:06:00,090 --> 00:06:04,960
I haven't done anything to feel guilty about.

65
00:06:04,960 --> 00:06:09,070
If you don't believe me,
you can call the police.

66
00:06:09,070 --> 00:06:12,410
- What? We'll call them then...
- Rina.

67
00:06:14,200 --> 00:06:16,900
I'm fine, don't worry.

68
00:06:16,900 --> 00:06:20,160
- Jeez, Anna, you're just too nice.
- Yeah.

69
00:06:20,160 --> 00:06:21,590
That's not true at all.

70
00:06:21,590 --> 00:06:23,730
I'd never let it go.

71
00:06:31,000 --> 00:06:32,950
[Thanks for the other day. Are you okay?
Did you make up with your members?]

72
00:06:32,950 --> 00:06:35,750
<i>I think they still don't believe me.</i>

73
00:06:36,350 --> 00:06:38,360
<i>But I'll keep trying.</i>

74
00:06:42,870 --> 00:06:46,266
[Diamond heart necklace]

75
00:06:50,830 --> 00:06:52,870
[Ama]

76
00:07:08,040 --> 00:07:10,390
Oh, you're here.

77
00:07:14,170 --> 00:07:17,150
By the way, I saw Kairi yesterday.

78
00:07:17,150 --> 00:07:20,410
He was pouting
because you've been distant lately.

79
00:07:20,410 --> 00:07:22,500
I bet.

80
00:07:22,500 --> 00:07:25,111
I stopped doing that stuff.

81
00:07:25,111 --> 00:07:26,176
Huh?

82
00:07:26,176 --> 00:07:27,690
[Ama]

83
00:07:30,900 --> 00:07:33,940
Oh, Ama?

84
00:07:34,580 --> 00:07:36,610
Yeah.

85
00:07:36,610 --> 00:07:39,560
There's something I want
to talk to you about,

86
00:07:39,560 --> 00:07:42,120
so I was hoping to see you tomorrow.

87
00:07:43,070 --> 00:07:46,330
Then I'll go pick you up.

88
00:07:46,330 --> 00:07:48,970
See you tomorrow.

89
00:07:51,700 --> 00:07:56,440
You're... on the phone with a girl.

90
00:07:57,100 --> 00:08:01,400
You always say things like,
"Calls and texts are a pain".

91
00:08:01,400 --> 00:08:04,510
"Is communication necessary anywhere
but in bed?"

92
00:08:04,510 --> 00:08:06,210
And you'd block them immediately.

93
00:08:06,210 --> 00:08:08,660
They're still a pain now.

94
00:08:08,660 --> 00:08:11,230
But Ama is different.

95
00:08:11,850 --> 00:08:15,210
I actually wonder what she's doing right now.

96
00:08:16,040 --> 00:08:17,450
Why?

97
00:08:18,100 --> 00:08:20,130
"Why"?

98
00:08:21,490 --> 00:08:22,630
Since when?

99
00:08:22,630 --> 00:08:25,470
When did this start?

100
00:08:27,990 --> 00:08:29,850
It started...

101
00:08:33,160 --> 00:08:35,510
<i>when she got hit.</i>

102
00:08:35,510 --> 00:08:37,060
<i>Huh?</i>

103
00:08:38,060 --> 00:08:40,090
For my sake.

104
00:08:41,980 --> 00:08:43,490
By my mother.

105
00:08:43,490 --> 00:08:44,670
What?

106
00:08:44,670 --> 00:08:47,240
Tell me the details!

107
00:08:49,320 --> 00:08:50,730
Okay.

108
00:08:57,540 --> 00:08:59,170
What?

109
00:09:01,560 --> 00:09:05,590
Chiaki, you like that girl, don't you?

110
00:09:07,880 --> 00:09:09,660
Like?

111
00:09:09,660 --> 00:09:10,930
Yeah.

112
00:09:13,740 --> 00:09:17,065
I think this calls for a good drink!

113
00:09:17,065 --> 00:09:20,995
Barkeep, give me your most expensive drink.

114
00:09:28,720 --> 00:09:30,460
Sorry to keep you waiting.

115
00:09:30,460 --> 00:09:32,740
No, not at all.

116
00:09:33,600 --> 00:09:36,770
So, what did you want to talk about?

117
00:09:49,410 --> 00:09:53,710
What's this about, calling me out like this?

118
00:09:53,710 --> 00:09:57,780
Saotome, I wanted to talk to you properly.

119
00:09:57,780 --> 00:10:00,840
I don't want to talk to a thief.

120
00:10:00,840 --> 00:10:05,380
I really didn't steal your necklace.

121
00:10:10,400 --> 00:10:14,170
Who's going to believe
anything you say now?

122
00:10:14,880 --> 00:10:19,870
You don't have any proof that I stole it.

123
00:10:24,640 --> 00:10:27,090
Excuse me.

124
00:10:27,090 --> 00:10:29,040
Hello?

125
00:10:30,120 --> 00:10:31,500
Yeah.

126
00:11:04,600 --> 00:11:09,250
That necklace...
Isn't that the one you said you lost?

127
00:11:10,840 --> 00:11:13,610
Why did you lie about that?

128
00:11:23,240 --> 00:11:26,440
You're such an eyesore!

129
00:11:27,280 --> 00:11:29,530
Why does the lowest-ranking member
of our group

130
00:11:29,530 --> 00:11:31,990
get all the good breaks?

131
00:11:31,990 --> 00:11:34,120
"Oh, I can't do anything."

132
00:11:34,120 --> 00:11:37,380
But then you take all the good gigs.

133
00:11:37,380 --> 00:11:40,900
People like you are the worst!

134
00:11:40,900 --> 00:11:42,640
Saotome.

135
00:11:42,640 --> 00:11:46,150
Why don't you tell
the other members about this?

136
00:11:49,184 --> 00:11:52,834
Not that anyone would believe you.

137
00:11:57,690 --> 00:12:00,340
After all, everyone hates you.

138
00:12:01,950 --> 00:12:03,520
Disappear.

139
00:12:04,540 --> 00:12:08,390
Disappear, disappear, disappear!

140
00:12:16,612 --> 00:12:20,712
Get out of my sight!

141
00:12:39,160 --> 00:12:43,150
I recorded all of that.

142
00:12:43,150 --> 00:12:44,520
Huh?

143
00:12:44,520 --> 00:12:49,390
I sent this to your manager.

144
00:13:02,910 --> 00:13:04,890
Good.

145
00:13:04,890 --> 00:13:06,650
It worked out.

146
00:13:10,940 --> 00:13:15,130
Mr. Chiaki, thank you so much.

147
00:13:15,130 --> 00:13:16,760
No problem.

148
00:13:17,430 --> 00:13:22,497
If it weren't for you,
who knows what would've happened?

149
00:13:23,513 --> 00:13:26,850
So, what did you want to talk about?

150
00:13:28,240 --> 00:13:32,650
Actually, I saw something interesting.

151
00:13:33,910 --> 00:13:39,030
I think this is
Anna Saotome's private account.

152
00:13:39,030 --> 00:13:43,460
That's the necklace she said she lost.

153
00:13:43,460 --> 00:13:45,230
Hey, Ama.

154
00:13:46,150 --> 00:13:48,710
Do you trust me?

155
00:13:49,450 --> 00:13:52,850
Who's going to believe anything you say now?

156
00:13:54,900 --> 00:13:56,540
[Mr. Chiaki]

157
00:13:56,540 --> 00:13:58,120
Excuse me.

158
00:13:59,020 --> 00:14:00,210
Hello?

159
00:14:00,210 --> 00:14:01,800
<i>Step out for a moment.</i>

160
00:14:01,800 --> 00:14:03,300
Okay.

161
00:14:04,240 --> 00:14:07,170
<i>Keep talking.</i>

162
00:14:07,170 --> 00:14:09,250
As loud as you can.

163
00:14:09,250 --> 00:14:10,870
<i>Okay.</i>

164
00:14:10,870 --> 00:14:14,010
Well, about the upcoming filming,

165
00:14:14,010 --> 00:14:16,980
there's something I wanted to ask you.

166
00:14:17,990 --> 00:14:22,530
I never imagined Saotome
felt that way about me.

167
00:14:24,370 --> 00:14:27,420
You're too pure.

168
00:14:27,420 --> 00:14:28,800
Huh?

169
00:14:29,400 --> 00:14:30,930
In this world,

170
00:14:30,930 --> 00:14:35,600
the more popular you get,
the more people try to drag you down.

171
00:14:37,410 --> 00:14:39,850
But it's okay.

172
00:14:39,850 --> 00:14:42,620
I'll stay by your side.

173
00:14:44,000 --> 00:14:46,680
Thank you.

174
00:14:46,680 --> 00:14:50,860
Our shoot together is almost over, right?

175
00:14:50,860 --> 00:14:52,650
Yeah.

176
00:14:52,650 --> 00:14:53,740
Oh, right.

177
00:14:53,740 --> 00:14:58,660
I actually have a new drama lined up.

178
00:14:58,660 --> 00:15:00,900
Oh, that's great.

179
00:15:00,900 --> 00:15:04,480
And I also got an offer
to audition for a movie,

180
00:15:04,480 --> 00:15:07,460
so I think I'm going to try it.

181
00:15:07,460 --> 00:15:12,370
I realized I really do like acting.

182
00:15:12,370 --> 00:15:15,790
I want to keep
challenging myself from now on.

183
00:15:15,790 --> 00:15:18,920
I'm so grateful to you
for making me realize...

184
00:15:18,920 --> 00:15:20,360
I don't like that.

185
00:15:22,440 --> 00:15:26,550
The thought of you being on set without me.

186
00:15:27,330 --> 00:15:28,750
Huh?

187
00:15:31,550 --> 00:15:33,540
Mr. Chiaki?

188
00:15:36,060 --> 00:15:39,000
Don't talk to other actors.

189
00:15:40,220 --> 00:15:41,810
Ignore them.

190
00:15:48,410 --> 00:15:51,830
And don't exchange contact info with anyone.

191
00:15:51,830 --> 00:15:55,000
Come straight home after filming ends.

192
00:15:56,630 --> 00:15:58,860
Oh, right.

193
00:15:58,860 --> 00:16:02,220
You should always have your manager get you.

194
00:16:03,760 --> 00:16:06,919
No, it'd be better if I pick you up.

195
00:16:06,919 --> 00:16:08,559
Mr. Chiaki?

196
00:16:10,850 --> 00:16:12,930
What's wrong?

197
00:16:15,150 --> 00:16:16,510
Sorry.

198
00:16:17,630 --> 00:16:20,920
You're so cute, it worries me.

199
00:16:20,920 --> 00:16:23,370
I'm not...

200
00:16:23,370 --> 00:16:26,780
You're cuter than anyone, Ama.

201
00:16:28,690 --> 00:16:29,840
<i>Listen, okay?</i>

202
00:16:29,840 --> 00:16:31,960
No matter how close you get to him,

203
00:16:31,960 --> 00:16:35,390
don't make any mistakes
with Mr. Hosho, alright?

204
00:16:37,530 --> 00:16:40,650
<i>Mr. Chiaki is kind.</i>

205
00:16:40,650 --> 00:16:45,040
<i>That's the only reason he said those things.</i>

206
00:16:48,380 --> 00:16:50,580
I heard from Mr. Suzui.

207
00:16:50,580 --> 00:16:53,280
Anna is seriously messed up.

208
00:16:53,280 --> 00:16:56,060
But I always knew she had a dark side.

209
00:16:56,060 --> 00:16:58,440
I heard Anna is leaving the group,

210
00:16:58,440 --> 00:17:00,770
so let's do our best, three of us!

211
00:17:00,770 --> 00:17:02,380
Let's do our best!

212
00:17:02,380 --> 00:17:04,835
- I'm really sorry for everything.
- I'm really sorry.

213
00:17:04,835 --> 00:17:07,521
[Thicket and the Flower Basket]
[Auditions]

214
00:17:11,739 --> 00:17:14,290
I'm filming in the studio
next door right now.

215
00:17:14,290 --> 00:17:16,570
Join one of my projects again.

216
00:17:16,570 --> 00:17:18,670
I really want to, Director.

217
00:17:18,670 --> 00:17:20,490
Glad to hear it.

218
00:17:22,700 --> 00:17:24,260
Ama.

219
00:17:31,100 --> 00:17:32,480
Ama?

220
00:17:37,910 --> 00:17:40,750
Those auditioning, please come this way.

221
00:17:52,040 --> 00:17:54,170
Thank you very much.

222
00:17:58,730 --> 00:18:00,170
Ama!

223
00:18:10,760 --> 00:18:12,220
I've...

224
00:18:12,990 --> 00:18:15,470
I've always wanted to apologize to you, Ama.

225
00:18:18,530 --> 00:18:22,390
Just once, let me talk to you.

226
00:18:25,230 --> 00:18:27,700
Please contact me.

227
00:18:28,710 --> 00:18:30,110
See you.

228
00:18:38,030 --> 00:18:42,730
<i>I knew Kairi had become an actor.</i>

229
00:18:42,730 --> 00:18:44,290
<i>But...</i>

230
00:18:48,060 --> 00:18:49,670
<i>Please don't.</i>

231
00:18:52,740 --> 00:18:54,780
<i>I thought he was a distant presence,</i>

232
00:18:54,780 --> 00:18:57,930
<i>someone I'd never have to deal with again.</i>

233
00:19:01,265 --> 00:19:04,144
[Mr. Chiaki]
<i>Can you meet today?</i>

234
00:19:11,020 --> 00:19:15,160
Wow, this is a beautiful place.

235
00:19:15,160 --> 00:19:19,220
I wanted to show you this view.

236
00:19:19,970 --> 00:19:22,290
Thank you.

237
00:19:28,707 --> 00:19:32,097
Ama, did something happen?

238
00:19:33,250 --> 00:19:35,390
You can tell me.

239
00:19:37,460 --> 00:19:39,340
Well...

240
00:19:39,340 --> 00:19:45,450
I bumped into someone
I had a falling out with in high school.

241
00:19:45,450 --> 00:19:47,520
A falling out?

242
00:19:48,980 --> 00:19:52,080
That person tried to apologize,

243
00:19:52,080 --> 00:19:54,610
but I ended up running away.

244
00:19:57,490 --> 00:20:01,990
Are you still angry at that person?

245
00:20:01,990 --> 00:20:03,650
No.

246
00:20:04,260 --> 00:20:06,260
It's more than that.

247
00:20:06,260 --> 00:20:09,680
I'd rather he just forget about it.

248
00:20:11,530 --> 00:20:16,090
If you feel that way, why not tell him?

249
00:20:18,060 --> 00:20:20,230
It's okay.

250
00:20:20,230 --> 00:20:23,380
I believe in you.

251
00:20:29,540 --> 00:20:31,420
Thank you.

252
00:20:31,420 --> 00:20:34,030
I'll try to properly tell him.

253
00:20:39,980 --> 00:20:41,810
Oh, right.

254
00:20:41,810 --> 00:20:44,740
That movie audition was today, right?

255
00:20:44,740 --> 00:20:49,250
Yeah, for Director Tanuma's new project.

256
00:20:49,250 --> 00:20:52,330
He helped me out
when I made my debut too.

257
00:20:53,240 --> 00:20:55,680
He's a good director.

258
00:20:55,680 --> 00:20:57,890
Oh, I see.

259
00:20:57,890 --> 00:21:00,100
I hope I get the part.

260
00:21:01,220 --> 00:21:04,390
What's the movie about?

261
00:21:05,550 --> 00:21:10,410
It's more of a mature romance, I think.

262
00:21:10,410 --> 00:21:14,410
I'm a little worried about
getting into character.

263
00:21:15,400 --> 00:21:19,830
I feel like I can only
really become a character

264
00:21:19,830 --> 00:21:24,580
if I've experienced something similar myself.

265
00:21:26,300 --> 00:21:28,710
Method acting, huh?

266
00:21:29,530 --> 00:21:32,000
Method acting?

267
00:21:33,450 --> 00:21:37,260
Acting by reliving your own emotions.

268
00:21:38,380 --> 00:21:41,470
Maybe you've been doing that naturally.

269
00:21:42,580 --> 00:21:44,420
I see.

270
00:21:45,970 --> 00:21:47,730
Hey.

271
00:21:47,730 --> 00:21:49,060
Yes?

272
00:21:52,840 --> 00:21:57,280
Was it the same, the first time you acted?

273
00:22:02,030 --> 00:22:04,180
<i>I love you.</i>

274
00:22:04,180 --> 00:22:07,950
<i>I've always loved you.</i>

275
00:22:11,348 --> 00:22:14,058
Yes, it was.

276
00:22:14,790 --> 00:22:19,910
So that's why I was able to do it that time.

277
00:22:28,590 --> 00:22:30,050
Who was it?

278
00:22:30,950 --> 00:22:32,250
Huh?

279
00:22:33,660 --> 00:22:38,190
Back then, who did you think of?

280
00:22:40,810 --> 00:22:45,880
Someone I liked back in school.

281
00:22:48,510 --> 00:22:50,920
I see.

282
00:22:50,920 --> 00:22:55,910
But, I've never been
in a mature relationship.

283
00:22:56,630 --> 00:22:59,000
What should I do?

284
00:23:04,890 --> 00:23:06,890
Then have one with me.

285
00:23:09,210 --> 00:23:10,680
Huh?

286
00:23:13,720 --> 00:23:15,510
Experience it all

287
00:23:16,350 --> 00:23:18,720
with me.

288
00:23:20,370 --> 00:23:22,040
Ama.

289
00:23:23,020 --> 00:23:25,160
Go out with me.

290
00:23:29,325 --> 00:23:31,370
I don't want anyone else to have you.

291
00:23:31,370 --> 00:23:34,829
To be honest, this is my first time
going out with someone.

292
00:23:34,829 --> 00:23:36,870
I was so surprised
that you became an actress.

293
00:23:36,870 --> 00:23:39,010
So I'll take on any role!

294
00:23:39,010 --> 00:23:40,990
My heart just skipped a beat.

295
00:23:40,990 --> 00:23:43,850
Ama, I love you.

